{
  "name": "Mass Summon",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "modules/pf1spheres/assets/icons/spheres/conjuration.webp",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>When you summon a companion, you may spend an additional spell point to summon an additional companion that you possess. You must spend 1 additional spell point per companion, but may summon up to 1 additional companion, +1 per 5 caster levels you possess as part of the same action.</p>\n<p>Additional costs to summon each companion must be paid separately, as well as spell points spent to allow the companions to endure without concentration. However, if you choose to maintain these summoned companions via concentration, you may maintain all companions summoned through Mass Summon as part of the same concentration action.</p>\n",
